    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The 4.72.2 update effectively displaced the issue. Now, the new issue: \"Cannot find namespace 'google'\" in a dozen places in nodes_modules/instantsearch.js/es/widgets/geo-search/geo-search.d.ts and nodes_modules/instantsearch.js/es/widgets/geo-search/createHTMLMarker.d.ts. \r\n\r\nAlso, in nodes_modules/instantsearch.js/es/widgets/geo-search/geo-search.d.ts, I get the following:\r\n\r\n- LIne 121:36 : Property 'google' does not exist on type 'Window & typeof globalThis'\r\n- Line 213:51 : Cannot find name 'google'\r\n\r\nEDIT1: Adding \"google.maps\" to the type section of tsconfig.app.json and tsconfig.spec.json solves those issues. However, it creates yet another issue in nodes_modules/instantsearch.js/es/widgets/geo-search/geo-search.d.ts, Line 213:63 \r\n`markerOptions: GeoSearchMarker<typeof google.maps.MarkerOptions | Partial<HTMLMarkerArguments>>;`, Property 'MarkerOptions' does not exist on type 'typeof maps'. \r\nThis compilation issue can be solved by removing `typeof` in the file, but it is only a bandaid for developpement that won't work for deployment.",
